    ],
    "lyrics": {
      "text": "While Ga-bri-el was say-ing Re-joice to thee, O Vir-gin, at his voice the Mas-ter of all things took flesh with-in thy pure womb. He dwelt in thee as His ho-ly ark, as spake the right-eous Da-vid in the psalms. And in bear-ing thy Cre-a--tor, thou wast shown forth more spa-cious than all the Heav--ens. Glo--ry to Him that willed to dwell in thee. Glo-ry to Him that came__ forth from thee. Glo--ry to Him that, through thy bring-ing forth,__ hath de-liv--ered__ us."
    }
